Absa Bank Kenya last Wednesday celebrated the official opening of its Mombasa branches with a colourful cocktail party at the historical Fort Jesus. The event titled ‘A Night of a Thousand Lights’ was attended by individuals from the corporate sector, county government and business people. They included Absa Kenya CEO Jeremy Awori, Absa Kenya chairperson Charles Munene, Mombasa county chief of staff Joab Tumbo, and chief officers Innocent Mugabe (Education) and Ilhan Abbas (Environment).